Performance-Critical Situations

Scenario: Font Performance Optimization

When website performance is critical, developers need to analyze and optimize font loading strategies.

// Font performance optimizer
class FontPerformanceOptimizer {
    constructor() {
        this.metrics = {
            loadTimes: [],
            sizes: [],
            renderBlocking: [],
            cacheStatus: []
        };
        this.optimizations = [];
    }
    
    async analyzePerformance() {
        console.log('⚡ Analyzing font performance...');
        
        // Collect font metrics
        await this.collectMetrics();
        
        // Analyze loading patterns
        this.analyzeLoadingPatterns();
        
        // Check caching strategies
        this.analyzeCaching();
        
        // Generate optimization recommendations
        this.generateOptimizations();
        
        // Create performance report
        this.generatePerformanceReport();
    }
    
    async collectMetrics() {
        const fontEntries = performance.getEntriesByType('resource')
            .filter(e => /\.(woff2?|ttf|otf|eot)(\?.*)?$/i.test(e.name));
        
        for (const entry of fontEntries) {
            const metrics = {
                url: entry.name,
                filename: entry.name.split('/').pop().split('?')[0],
                size: entry.transferSize || 0,
                loadTime: entry.duration || 0,
                startTime: entry.startTime,
                responseStart: entry.responseStart,
                responseEnd: entry.responseEnd,
                cached: entry.transferSize === 0 && entry.decodedBodySize > 0
            };
            
            // Check if font is render-blocking
            metrics.renderBlocking = await this.checkRenderBlocking(entry.name);
            
            // Analyze font format efficiency
            metrics.formatEfficiency = this.analyzeFormat(metrics.filename);
            
            this.metrics.loadTimes.push(metrics.loadTime);
            this.metrics.sizes.push(metrics.size);
            
            if (metrics.renderBlocking) {
                this.metrics.renderBlocking.push(metrics);
            }
            
            this.metrics.cacheStatus.push({
                url: metrics.url,
                cached: metrics.cached,
                size: metrics.size
            });
        }
    }
    
    async checkRenderBlocking(fontUrl) {
        // Check if font is loaded synchronously in CSS
        try {
            const stylesheets = Array.from(document.styleSheets);
            
            for (const sheet of stylesheets) {
                try {
                    const rules = Array.from(sheet.cssRules || []);
                    
                    for (const rule of rules) {
                        if (rule.type === CSSRule.FONT_FACE_RULE) {
                            const src = rule.style.src;
                            if (src && src.includes(fontUrl.split('/').pop())) {
                                // Check if font-display is set
                                const fontDisplay = rule.style.fontDisplay;
                                return !fontDisplay || fontDisplay === 'auto' || fontDisplay === 'block';
                            }
                        }
                    }
                } catch (e) {
                    // Skip inaccessible stylesheets
                }
            }
        } catch (e) {
            console.warn('Could not analyze render blocking:', e);
        }
        
        return false;
    }
    
    analyzeFormat(filename) {
        const format = filename.split('.').pop().toLowerCase();
        
        const formatScores = {
            'woff2': 100, // Best compression
            'woff': 80,   // Good compression
            'ttf': 60,    // Larger files
            'otf': 60,    // Larger files
            'eot': 40     // Legacy format
        };
        
        return {
            format,
            score: formatScores[format] || 50,
            recommendation: this.getFormatRecommendation(format)
        };
    }
    
    getFormatRecommendation(format) {
        switch (format) {
            case 'woff2':
                return 'Optimal format - no changes needed';
            case 'woff':
                return 'Consider upgrading to WOFF2 for better compression';
            case 'ttf':
            case 'otf':
                return 'Convert to WOFF2 for web use - significant size reduction possible';
            case 'eot':
                return 'Legacy format - replace with WOFF2/WOFF for modern browsers';
            default:
                return 'Unknown format - verify browser support';
        }
    }
    
    analyzeLoadingPatterns() {
        console.log('📊 Analyzing font loading patterns...');
        
        const avgLoadTime = this.metrics.loadTimes.reduce((a, b) => a + b, 0) / this.metrics.loadTimes.length;
        const totalSize = this.metrics.sizes.reduce((a, b) => a + b, 0);
        const maxLoadTime = Math.max(...this.metrics.loadTimes);
        
        console.log(`Average load time: ${avgLoadTime.toFixed(2)}ms`);
        console.log(`Total font size: ${(totalSize / 1024).toFixed(1)}KB`);
        console.log(`Slowest font: ${maxLoadTime.toFixed(2)}ms`);
        
        // Performance thresholds
        if (avgLoadTime > 1000) {
            this.optimizations.push({
                type: 'loading',
                priority: 'high',
                issue: 'Slow average font loading time',
                solution: 'Implement font preloading and optimize font files'
            });
        }
        
        if (totalSize > 500 * 1024) {
            this.optimizations.push({
                type: 'size',
                priority: 'high',
                issue: 'Large total font size',
                solution: 'Reduce number of fonts or implement font subsetting'
            });
        }
        
        if (this.metrics.renderBlocking.length > 0) {
            this.optimizations.push({
                type: 'rendering',
                priority: 'critical',
                issue: 'Render-blocking fonts detected',
                solution: 'Add font-display: swap to @font-face rules'
            });
        }
    }
    
    analyzeCaching() {
        console.log('💾 Analyzing font caching...');
        
        const cachedFonts = this.metrics.cacheStatus.filter(font => font.cached);
        const uncachedFonts = this.metrics.cacheStatus.filter(font => !font.cached);
        
        console.log(`Cached fonts: ${cachedFonts.length}`);
        console.log(`Uncached fonts: ${uncachedFonts.length}`);
        
        if (uncachedFonts.length > 0) {
            this.optimizations.push({
                type: 'caching',
                priority: 'medium',
                issue: 'Fonts not being cached effectively',
                solution: 'Implement proper cache headers and consider service worker caching'
            });
        }
    }
    
    generateOptimizations() {
        console.log('🔧 Generating optimization recommendations...');
        
        // Add general optimizations
        this.optimizations.push(
            {
                type: 'preloading',
                priority: 'medium',
                issue: 'Critical fonts not preloaded',
                solution: 'Add <link rel="preload" as="font" type="font/woff2" href="font.woff2" crossorigin> for critical fonts',
                code: '<link rel="preload" as="font" type="font/woff2" href="critical-font.woff2" crossorigin>'
            },
            {
                type: 'fallbacks',
                priority: 'medium',
                issue: 'Font fallbacks not optimized',
                solution: 'Use system font fallbacks to reduce layout shift',
                code: 'font-family: "Custom Font", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, sans-serif;'
            },
            {
                type: 'display',
                priority: 'high',
                issue: 'Font display strategy not optimized',
                solution: 'Use font-display: swap for better loading experience',
                code: '@font-face { font-family: "MyFont"; src: url("font.woff2"); font-display: swap; }'
            }
        );
    }
    
    generatePerformanceReport() {
        console.log('\n⚡ FONT PERFORMANCE REPORT');
        console.log('=' .repeat(50));
        
        // Summary metrics
        const avgLoadTime = this.metrics.loadTimes.reduce((a, b) => a + b, 0) / this.metrics.loadTimes.length;
        const totalSize = this.metrics.sizes.reduce((a, b) => a + b, 0);
        
        console.log('📊 PERFORMANCE METRICS:');
        console.log(`Total Fonts: ${this.metrics.loadTimes.length}`);
        console.log(`Average Load Time: ${avgLoadTime.toFixed(2)}ms`);
        console.log(`Total Size: ${(totalSize / 1024).toFixed(1)}KB`);
        console.log(`Cached Fonts: ${this.metrics.cacheStatus.filter(f => f.cached).length}`);
        console.log(`Render Blocking: ${this.metrics.renderBlocking.length}`);
        console.log('');
        
        // Performance score
        let score = 100;
        if (avgLoadTime > 1000) score -= 20;
        if (totalSize > 500 * 1024) score -= 20;
        if (this.metrics.renderBlocking.length > 0) score -= 30;
        if (this.metrics.cacheStatus.filter(f => !f.cached).length > 0) score -= 10;
        
        console.log(`🎯 PERFORMANCE SCORE: ${Math.max(0, score)}/100`);
        console.log('');
        
        // Optimizations
        if (this.optimizations.length > 0) {
            console.log('🔧 OPTIMIZATION RECOMMENDATIONS:');
            this.optimizations.forEach((opt, index) => {
                console.log(`${index + 1}. [${opt.priority.toUpperCase()}] ${opt.issue}`);
                console.log(`   Solution: ${opt.solution}`);
                if (opt.code) {
                    console.log(`   Code: ${opt.code}`);
                }
                console.log('');
            });
        }
        
        // Implementation guide
        console.log('📋 IMPLEMENTATION CHECKLIST:');
        console.log('□ Add font-display: swap to all @font-face rules');
        console.log('□ Preload critical fonts with <link rel="preload">');
        console.log('□ Implement proper font fallbacks');
        console.log('□ Set up font caching headers');
        console.log('□ Consider font subsetting for unused characters');
        console.log('□ Use WOFF2 format for modern browsers');
        console.log('□ Monitor Core Web Vitals impact');
    }
    
    // Generate optimized CSS
    generateOptimizedCSS() {
        let css = '/* Optimized Font Loading CSS */\n\n';
        
        // Add preload hints
        css += '<!-- Add to <head> section -->\n';
        this.metrics.cacheStatus.slice(0, 2).forEach(font => {
            const filename = font.url.split('/').pop().split('?')[0];
            if (filename.endsWith('.woff2')) {
                css += `<link rel="preload" as="font" type="font/woff2" href="${font.url}" crossorigin>\n`;
            }
        });
        css += '\n';
        
        // Add optimized @font-face rules
        css += '/* Optimized @font-face rules */\n';
        css += '@font-face {\n';
        css += '  font-family: "OptimizedFont";\n';
        css += '  src: url("font.woff2") format("woff2"),\n';
        css += '       url("font.woff") format("woff");\n';
        css += '  font-display: swap;\n';
        css += '  font-weight: 400;\n';
        css += '  font-style: normal;\n';
        css += '}\n\n';
        
        // Add fallback strategies
        css += '/* Optimized font stacks */\n';
        css += '.text-primary {\n';
        css += '  font-family: "OptimizedFont", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, sans-serif;\n';
        css += '}\n\n';
        
        // Download CSS file
        const blob = new Blob([css], { type: 'text/css' });
        const link = document.createElement('a');
        link.href = URL.createObjectURL(blob);
        link.download = 'optimized-fonts.css';
        link.click();
        URL.revokeObjectURL(link.href);
        
        console.log('📄 Optimized CSS file downloaded');
    }
}

  • Font Conversion: Convert between font formats (TTF to WOFF2, OTF to WOFF) using online tools or command-line utilities like fonttools
  • Font Subsetting: Remove unused characters from font files to reduce file size using tools like Glyphhanger or FontSquirrel

Frequently Asked Questions

Q: Which method should I choose?

A: For beginners or one-time extraction, use the Network Tab method - it’s the most straightforward and works reliably. For developers who regularly work with fonts, the Application Tab method provides better organization. If you need to extract fonts from multiple sites or want automation, use Console Scripts. For professional designers, Browser Extensions offer the best user experience.

Q: What about browser compatibility?

A: All methods work in Chrome 70+, but newer versions offer better features. The Network Tab and Sources Panel methods have the widest compatibility. Application Tab features are best in Chrome 88+. Console Scripts work in any modern Chrome version. Always test your chosen method in your target Chrome version.

Q: How do I handle edge cases?

A: Common edge cases include: fonts loaded after user interaction (use dynamic monitoring scripts), base64-encoded fonts in CSS (extract from stylesheet source), and fonts behind authentication (ensure you’re logged in). For fonts that don’t appear immediately, try interacting with the page (scroll, click) then re-run your extraction method.

Q: Are there performance differences?

A: Yes, significant differences exist. Console Scripts are fastest for bulk operations (5-10 seconds for multiple fonts). Manual methods (Network/Application tabs) take 20-45 seconds depending on complexity. Browser Extensions offer the best balance of speed and usability. Consider your use case: one-time extraction vs. regular workflow.

Q: Can I combine multiple approaches?

A: Absolutely! A hybrid approach often works best. Start with the Network Tab for quick identification, use Console Scripts for bulk downloading, and employ Browser Extensions for ongoing font management. Many professionals use the Application Tab for analysis and Console Scripts for automation within the same workflow.

function runExtraction() {
